SwiftGUDHIFull / GudhiCoreFull — licensing
==========================================

Original source in this repository (the facade / build scripts) is authored by
Hiroaki Yamane (mnmly) and offered under the MIT License (below).

HOWEVER, the COMPILED BINARY produced by this branch — `GudhiCoreFull.xcframework`
— statically links CGAL packages that are licensed GPL-3.0-or-later (the dD
triangulation used by the Alpha, Tangential and Euclidean Witness modules), plus
GMP/MPFR (LGPL-3.0). Therefore the binary as a whole, and any application that
links it, is governed by **GPL-3.0-or-later** (see LICENSE.GPL-3.0). Distributing
an application linked against GudhiCoreFull.xcframework requires complying with
the GPL: the application must itself be GPL-3.0-compatible and its complete
source made available. It cannot be used in closed-source / App Store apps.

For a permissive (MIT/BSD) binary without the CGAL modules, use the `main`
branch / the `SwiftGUDHI` package and `GudhiCore.xcframework`.

See THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md for the full component inventory.

